21 September 2009 }}, Myrel Elaine Moss  (Sister Moss), golocaljamaica.com, 2003-01-01.</ref>\n{{quote|Back in the days of plantation slavery in Jamaica, the Chapleton locality was a plantocracy settlement. Instead of going to church in the capital May Pen, the plantation owners built a church in Chapleton where they worshiped. Local folk therefore talked about going to \u201cthe chapel in the town.\u201d After a while, the town became known as Chapel Town but with the passing of time, the name became distorted and was shortened to become Chapelton.}}\n\n==Amenities==\n*[[Clarendon College (Jamaica)|Clarendon College]], secondary school.\n*[[List of hospitals in Jamaica#Clarendon Parish|Clarendon Hospital]], built c1903, now a community Type 3 hospital.<ref name=\"GoJa\"/>\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110927124947/http://www.golocaljamaica.com/photogallery/clarendon/1/images/Chapelton%20-%20police%20station.jpg Police Station].\n*St Paul's Anglican Church, founded over 300 years ago.<ref>[http://picasaweb.google.com/kathyalison/TheJamaicaFewSeeClarendonPictures#5287303263347504402 Kathy Alison]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, Picasa, 2009-01-03.</ref>\n\n==Transport==\n\n===Road===\nChapelton is on the [[Roads in Jamaica#B Roads|B3 road]] which climbs up from May Pen in the south, passes through the center of the town and continues north towards [[Brown's Town]].<ref name=\"G&H\">UK Directorate of Overseas Surveys 1:50,000 map of Jamaica Sheets G & H, 1973.</ref>\n\n===Rail===\nFrom 1925 to 1974 Chapelton was served by [[Chapelton railway station, Jamaica|Chapelton railway station]] on the [[Railways of Jamaica: May Pen to Frankfield|21 mile railway branch line]] from [[May Pen]] to [[Frankfield]].{{citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\n==Notable people from Chapelton==\n*[[Linton Kwesi Johnson]]\n*[[Raphael Morgan]] (Robert Josias Morgan)\n*[[Jah Shaka]]\n*[[Barrington Levy]]\n*[[Toots Hibbert]]\n*[[Freddie McGregor]]\n*[[Dennis Alcapone]]\n*[[Everton Blender]]\n*[[Levi Roots]]\n*[[Cocoa Tea]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of cities and towns in Jamaica]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* Photos: [https://web.archive.org/web/20110927125001/http://www.golocaljamaica.com/photogallery/clarendon/1/images/Chapelton%20Square.jpg] [https://web.archive.org/web/20101010224503/http://golocaljamaica.com/imgz/Chapenton1.JPG] [https://web.archive.org/web/20101010231133/http://golocaljamaica.com/imgz/chapelton%20-%20iron%20house.JPG] [https://web.archive.org/web/20120614074321/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20071206/news/images/Layout1_1_PIEICChapletoAM.jpg] [http://www.discoverjamaica.com/gallery/photoinfo.php?imgurl=ChapeltonA20060217NG.jpg] [https://web.archive.org/web/20111004211847/http://lh5.ggpht.com/_N4XgtjtFOds/SWBEKVzL6OI/AAAAAAAAACU/cYyoRrPEd7U/s640/IMG_0906.JPG] [https://web.archive.org/web/20111004211930/http://lh5.ggpht.com/_N4XgtjtFOds/SWBGJV0ruvI/AAAAAAAAAC4/Dtov4aW3Bnw/s640/IMG_0907.JPG] [https://web.archive.org/web/20111004211945/http://lh5.ggpht.com/_N4XgtjtFOds/SWBGTf-XdRI/AAAAAAAAADA/gTRs6XNwnjg/s640/IMG_0908.JPG] [https://web.archive.org/web/20111004211959/http://lh5.ggpht.com/_N4XgtjtFOds/SWBGfW338BI/AAAAAAAAADE/blhPMOVxOag/s640/IMG_0909.JPG].\n\n{{Settlements in Jamaica}}\n\n[[Category:Year of establishment missing]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Jamaica]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Clarendon Parish, Jamaica]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Jamaican English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|name                    = Chapelton\n|settlement_type         = Market Town\n|image_skyline           = \n|imagesize               = \n|image_alt               = \n|image_caption           = \n|image_flag              = \n|flag_size               = \n|flag_alt                = \n|image_seal              = \n|seal_size            